title.$t: OPRAH WINFREY'S NETWORK: REEL WORLD WITH MICA RUNWAY

media$title.$t: OPRAH WINFREY'S NETWORK: REEL WORLD WITH MICA RUNWAY

media$description.$t:
PLEASE CAST YOUR VOTE FOR MY OWN SHOW, "REEL WORLD WITH MICA RUNWAY FOR A SPOT ON OPRAH WINFREY'S NEW NETWORK.  

MY VIDEO DESCRIPTION

A Reality TV Talk Show, which focuses on the lives of (deaf and nondeaf) emerging models and designers priming for a production fashion show, MICA Runway and is hosted by a deaf model, Jubil Khan. Only the top 24 models (from a pool of 100 eliminated contestants) will get to participate in the finale fashion show. As we eliminate contestants weekly, we invite them on the show, interviewed by the host and show clip overviews of their work. Similar process will take place in selecting designers. One designer will create the theme collection for the show finale. 

A team of passionate Deaf and Hard-of-Hearing fashionistas with big dreams created Reel World with MICA Runway . There are Deaf and Hard-of-Hearing talents with dreams to become models, fashion designers, make-up artists, etc. We are a group of creative people who want to share wealth of knowledge by exposing audience about Deaf culture on our show, in an environment of American Sign Language (ASL) while increasing awareness.

http://myown.oprah.com/audition/index.html?request=add_video&entity_id=208235547

title.$t: Developing MICA Runway 2008

media$title.$t: Developing MICA Runway 2008

media$description.$t:
MICA RUNWAY is the leading arts and entertainment high-end event in New York City exclusively dedicated to showcasing works by emerging filmmakers, up-and-coming fashion designers, striving talents, literary and visual artists who utilize American Sign Language (ASL). MICA RUNWAY strives to provide access to the film, fashion, art and visual art worlds for these individuals who may be intimidated, oppressed or ignored by the gatekeepers of the elite art, fashion and entertainment industries. 

COME AND CELEBRATE MICA RUNWAY 2010 (10 YEAR ANNIVERSARY) WITH US THIS OCTOBER, 8-10, 2010!

media$description.$t:
MICA Scoop TV media covered USA Network's Character Approved event on February 25, 2010 to honor 10 individuals who are making impacts in America. Hundreds braved the snowstorm, just to celebrate, network and party.

Visit USA Network's website to learn about the honorees.

USA Network's Character Approved Awards honor the real characters who are changing the face of American Culture. Character Approved honorees are innovators in their field who influence our opinions, our style, and our view of the world. They surprise us and inspire us with fresh ideas. They are celebrated by their peers and they have an authentic style that's all their own.

Jade Films and Entertainment  MMX 2010

media$description.$t:
A brief introduction clips covering Mercedes-Benz Fashion Week featuring celebrities, backstage and front of house interviews, fashion shows and more!

KEEP YOUR EYES OUT FOR THE FINISH PRODUCT SOON!! THIS CLIP IS JUST A QUICK PREVIEW!

M I C A stands for Multicultural International Constorium (of Deaf and Hard-of-Hearing) Artists and Advocates

Check us out! 
http://micarunway.com
http://micascoop.blogspot.com

MICA CREW

Queen Jade - DP/MICA Creator
Diana Beato - Videophrapher/DP
Jubil Khan- Interviewer
Latoya Banks- Secondary Interviewer
Steve Martinez - Photographer
Nori Kuroda - Photographer

* MICA RUNWAY 2010 (September 2010)

MICA RUNWAY is a leading arts and entertainment high-end venture in New York City exclusively dedicated to showcasing works by emerging filmmakers, up-and-coming fashion designers, aspiring talent, literary and visual artists who are disabled, Deaf, Hard of Hearing or Deaf-Blind. 

Founded in 2000, MICA RUNWAY produces events such as film showcases, prominent fashion shows, art exhibitions, multimedia events, and much more. We have cultivated a loyal group of a hip, young generation (aged 18-39) who want to keep in touch with new developments in the arts and who strive to be in-the-know about the latest happenings and trends in the city.

title.$t: WHY DEAFVISION FILMWORKS NEEDS YOUR $25,000 VOTE/CHASE COMMUNITY GIVING

media$title.$t: WHY DEAFVISION FILMWORKS NEEDS YOUR $25,000 VOTE/CHASE COMMUNITY GIVING

media$description.$t:
Dear DeafVision Supporters, fans and friends!

Great News! We've just created a VLOG in ASL in English subtitles to help you understand the purpose of Chase Community Giving! Kudos to Maleni Chaitoo for contributing her time to help out!

Chase Bank is donating $25,000 to the 100 non-profit companies that get the most facebook votes! That's right. No gimmicks! There is not just one winner but one-hundred! I KNOW we can do this! And it only takes 20 seconds of your time to help our important cause.

This contest started on November 11th and ends December 11th. I found out about it last week, so we only have a week left to catch up. However... If EVERY PERSON who received this message and watch our vlog to learn about our goals casts one vote for DeafVision Filmworks, I believe we could be one of the top 100 companies! We would immediately have an operating fund for our projects and get the ball roling!! 

Voting for DeafVision Filmworks takes 20 seconds of your time and is easy!!

Tell your friends!!! Thanks for the support and the vote!

#1) Become a fan of Community Giving Facebook Page at:
http://www.facebook.com/l/62ba5;http://www.facebook.com/l/10ce2;tinyurl.com/ChaseFan

#2) Click on this link below for "DeafVision Filmworks and cast your vote (click the top button with the hand)!  http://apps.facebook.com/chasecommunitygiving/charities/1616?src=wallpost&ref=mf

#3) If you wish to make a donation to support our projects, click on this link: http://www.facebook.com/l/10ce2;www.jadefilm.com/vmpcampaign/donation.html

media$description.$t:
A Visual Music Project Campaign on a mission to educate those to create access to music videos or live events for deaf and hard of hearing consumers. It begins NOW! 

We promote equal access through partnership. Enjoy the video in American Sign Language! It's music for everybody.

VMP campaign project is not making money. We produced these videos to show the growing needs and the demands for accessibility to music videos and online playback contents.
